re book.

Neither suggestion makes sense. Google does not sell its scans, and the sca=
ns do not replace the books. While partner libraries have the ability to do=
wnload a scan of a book from their collections, they owned the books alread=
y =E2=80=94 they provided the original book to Google to scan. Nor is it li=
kely that someone would take the time and energy to input countless searche=
s to try and get enough snippets to comprise an entire book.

OpenAI does sell access to its large language models (along with Microsoft)=
; in this case Google=E2=80=99s search dominance, and the resultant luxury =
of not needing to monetize complements like Google Books, gave it more lega=
