Internet Value
--------------

Rufo was effective versus Harvard because he used their own rules about pla=
giarism against them; why, though, does Harvard have rules about plagiarism=
? I suspect it=E2=80=99s related to the fact that Harvard is 388 years old.=
 The goal is the accumulation of and passing on of knowledge, not just to t=
he students of today, but to the ones 300 years from now; that means that c=
areful attention to detail and honesty in one=E2=80=99s work today will sta=
nd the test of time, and add to Harvard=E2=80=99s legacy.

What is notable is that plagiarism is arguably the currency of the Internet=
. I wrote two years ago in Mistakes and Memes ( https://stratechery.com/202=
